Do you want to play this fun word game with me? After you watch the video, come up with your own word and put it in the comments! It’s addicting!

This word building activity will engage all your students while teaching prefixes, suffixes, spelling patterns, and new vocabulary! You can use this as a center or partner work, enrichment homework, whole or small group instruction, or even a five minute filler! If the link in my profile doesn’t work because it’s a video, message me for the link to this resource.  bit.ly/expandaword

This is how I group my students for remediation and it’s great for test prep groups/remediation. These formatives are a quick easy way to assess my math students. I created these rigorous mini-math assessments (five questions, one page) for each math standard in fourth grade. A (Form B) was also created to give my students another opportunity to show growth and learning. These tools drive my instruction and small group learning all year! 
Digital version with Google Slides and answer keys included.
5th grade is also available. 😊
Direct message me for the link to my TPT store, specify if you want 4th or 5th grade. #math #mathteacher #mathassessments

node.text:
We had our first student graduate from their multiplication facts last week! Once one person gets to take the lawn sign home and have a mini graduation ceremony, it sparks a fire and motivates other students to start practicing too. This is not for a grade, just an optional incentive to motivate some of my students to memorize their multiplication facts before we start multi-digit multiplication. 

It’s a quick timed test that takes less than a minute, some students get extra time. I do this every day at the beginning of our math block, quickly check for completion/grade some time during the day, and then students put a sticker on the chart to keep track of which fact they’re on.

*Students keep the sign for a few days and then return it. 

*Adding the link to the timed tests to my profile: bit.ly/multiplicationprogram

#multiplication #mathteacher #multiplicationfacts

Introduced our first MYSTERY PRIZE BOARD today! 🙌 Some of the tasks aren’t super difficult to achieve, just things I know we can improve on with some extra attention. I repeat the ones that need repeated practice. We brainstormed ways to earn these.

The best part of this incentive is I can customize it to tasks/behaviors I want to see more of in our classroom! Each time a student/class is caught completing the task, the sticky note is removed. The more they remove, the closer they get to the “mystery” prize. Sometimes it’s even more motivating when they’ve figured out the prize!
*Ssshh! Our first prize is the second pic. 😍

Scroll to see previous mystery prize boards! You can also just use numbers and when students are amazing, they can take one off!

Editable templates and printing instructions included in resource and available in my store. 😊
DIGITAL version also available! Link in my profile: bit.ly/mysteryprizeboard #classroommanagement 
@postit

node.text:
Now our class feels like a home. ❤️ I love how these posters line our classroom and welcome us each day. This activity has been one of my favorite activities for 25 years! I realized I was spending way too much money on pre-made posters from the teacher stores and I wanted our classroom to be OURS. This gives them a sense of ownership and it really brightens our room with their creativity! Each student picks a quote and interprets it and creates an illustration to represent it. It’s also a great project for early finishers to display their posters in the front office, cafeteria, etc. 

There’s over 100 poster quotes in this resource. Black and white backgrounds included.  Link to poster quotes in my profile. bit.ly/inspirationalquoteposters #backtoschool #classroomdecor

I introduced our first interactive game board today and let’s just say it was a hit!

It adds instant engagement to ANY lesson! Turn a simple worksheet into a game! When students answer a question or complete a task, they get to use their sticky notes! 

You can use any lesson, worksheet/workbook to play this game. Students answer questions, then place their sticky note! You can use them for brain teasers and behavior too! 

Games can be played in teams, partners, small groups, whole class, lots of possibilities!

*Tic Tac Toe from this year, other pics featuring other games are from last year.

My board is full and my heart is FULL! ❤️😍❤️

I’ve done this activity for about 16 years and every time we do this it fills everyone’s hearts who sees it. To see children celebrate their uniqueness, talents, and specialness is such a beautiful thing.

This is a simple way to build community and self-esteem in your We read the book “The Best Part of Me” as a model text and brainstormed the best parts of us to get ideas. I had so many students kids pick eyes this year! It’s interesting to see what kids love and appreciate about themselves! ❤️

Link in profile to step by step photo instructions, writing templates, and bulletin board letters included in resource. bit.ly/bestpartofmedirections
#bestpartofme #buildcommunity
